source: A generic key type to use for a password or API key that does not belong to any other defined key type.
A generic key type to use for an authentication key that contains multiple values.
A generic key type to use for an encryption key that does not belong to any other defined key type.
A human readable name for this override.
A key input for providers that don't accept a value.
A key input that generates a key value.
A key type to store a user/password pair.

A key value of the requested type has been generated and is displayed below as a Base64-encoded string. You will need to decode it to get the actual key value, which may or may not be human-readable. The key value will not be displayed again, so take note of it now, if necessary.
%key_value
A short description of the key.
Are you sure you want to delete the key %key?
Are you sure you want to delete the override %name?
Be extremely careful when deleting a key! It may result in losing access to a service or making encrypted data unreadable.
Be extremely careful when editing a key! It may result in broken site functionality. Are you sure you want to edit this key?
Be extremely careful when overwriting a key! It may result in losing access to a service or making encrypted data unreadable.
Check this field to clear any existing value for the overridden configuration item. This is important to make sure potentially sensitive data is removed from the configuration.
Check this if the key in the file is Base64-encoded.

Check this if the key in the variable is Base64-encoded. Note: Naturally Base64-encoded values, such as RSA keys, do not need to be marked as Base64-encoded unless they have been additionally encoded for another reason.
Check this if the key value being submitted has been Base64-encoded.
Check this to display the generated value once.
Check this to remove any trailing line breaks from the file. Leave unchecked if there is a chance that a line break could be a valid character in the key.
Check this to remove any trailing line breaks from the variable. Leave unchecked if there is a chance that a line break could be a valid character in the key.
Checking this will store the key with Base64 encoding.
Choose an available key. If the desired key is not listed, create a new key.
Create, edit, and delete site-wide keys.
Enter a custom key size in bits.
No key configuration overrides are available. Add an override.
No keys are available. Add a key.
Provides the ability to manage site-wide keys.
Settings specific to the defined key input, in JSON format.
Settings specific to the defined key provider, in JSON format.
Settings specific to the defined key type, in JSON format.
The Configuration key provider stores the key in Drupal's configuration system.
The Drush --storage-method option is deprecated in key:1.18.0 and is removed from key:2.0.0. Use the --tags option instead. See https://www.drupal.org/node/3364701
The Environment key provider allows a key to be retrieved from an environment variable.
The File key provider allows a key to be stored in a file, preferably outside of the web root.
The environment variable does not exist or it is empty.
The file at the specified location is not readable.
The following key will be deleted: !id
The following key will be overwritten: !id
The human-readable label of the key.
The key provider. To see a list of available key providers, use `drush key:provider-list`.
The key type. To see a list of available key types, use `drush key:type-list`.
The key value does not contain valid JSON.
The key value field %field is empty.
The key value has already been generated and will not be changed.
The key value is missing the field %field.
The key value will be automatically generated using the selected key type settings.
The location of the file in which the key will be stored. The path may be absolute (e.g., %abs), relative to the Drupal directory (e.g., %rel), or defined using a stream wrapper (e.g., %str).
The selected key provider does not accept a value. See the provider's description for instructions on how and where to store the key value.
The selected key size does not match the actual size of the key.
The size of the key in bits, with 8 bits per byte.
There is no file at the specified location.
